   This check ensures that the number of coupling steps does not exceed the number of channels. If it does, it indicates a configuration error that could lead to out-of-bounds access when processing audio data. By adding this validation, the code helps maintain the integrity of the audio processing logic and prevents potential crashes or undefined behavior.

